"title": "5210: arrows",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5210",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Pointed pieces of wood, shot from a bow, used in hunting and warfare. In the hands of skilful archers they are accurate and deadly weapons. Figuratively, they represent conviction and judgments from God, or the hurtful words of men and women.</p>\n<h2>Characteristics of arrows</h2>\n<h3>Deadly</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps64:3\">PSA 64:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:42\">DEU 32:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps7:13\">PSA 7:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek5:16\">EZK 5:16</a></p>\n<h3>Accurate</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs9:24\">2KI 9:24</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Sharp and piercing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:5\">PSA 45:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs9:24\">2KI 9:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job20:24\">JOB 20:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps120:4\">PSA 120:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:28\">ISA 5:28</a></p>\n<h2>Arrows used as a sign</h2>\n<h3>To warn David</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:19-1Sam20:22\">1SA 20:19–20:22</a></p>\n<h3>Of victory over Aram</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs13:17-2Kgs13:19\">2KI 13:17–13:19</a></p>\n<h3>Of divination by the Babylonians</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek21:21\">EZK 21:21</a></p>\n<h2>Arrows referred to figuratively</h2>\n<h3>To describe conviction from God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps38:2\">PSA 38:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job6:4\">JOB 6:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job34:6\">JOB 34:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:12-Lam3:13\">LAM 3:12–3:13</a></p>\n<h3>To describe judgment from God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps64:7\">PSA 64:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:23\">DEU 32:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:42\">DEU 32:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:5\">PSA 45:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek5:16\">EZK 5:16</a></p>\n<h3>To describe false accusations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps64:3-Ps64:4\">PSA 64:3–64:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps11:2\">PSA 11:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps57:4\">PSA 57:4</a></p>\n<h3>To describe false testimony</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:18\">PRO 25:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov26:18-Prov26:19\">PRO 26:18–26:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:3\">JER 9:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:8\">JER 9:8</a></p>\n<h3>To describe attacks of Satan</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:16\">EPH 6:16</a></strong></p>\n<h3>As lightning</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps77:17\">PSA 77:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:15\">2SA 22:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps144:6\">PSA 144:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech9:14\">ZEC 9:14</a></p>\n<h3>As sons as a blessing from God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps127:3-Ps127:5\">PSA 127:3–127:5</a></strong></p>",
